channel.title: Unexpected server response... TO EVERYONE?
channel.description: Sorry, couldn't think of better name. Whenever someone tries to log onto my server, it always says [i]Unexpected server response. Please use a different world.[/i] I never ip baned anyone and whenever I register my server on the server status page, it says its online. What's wrong?

item.title: Unexpected server response... TO EVERYONE?
item.dc:creator: @needhoster needhoster
item.description:
@needhoster wrote:

[quote="`Rich, post:8, topic:243030"][quote author=Coder xynt link=topic=319355.msg2530607#msg2530607 date=1226436280]

Sorry, couldn’t think of better name. Whenever someone tries to log onto my server, it always says Unexpected server response. Please use a different world. I never ip baned anyone and whenever I register my server on the server status page, it says its online. What’s wrong?
[/quote]Search your files (possibly server.java or client.java) and look for println("Unexpected server response. Please use a different world") And paste the whole code here.

Btw, what client are you using?

The message is client-side, the return code for that response is server-side.[/quote]makes no sense to me. soz
